16:09.236 --> 16:10.370
He thinks I suck.

16:10.437 --> 16:11.904
I don't know,
maybe he's right.

16:11.971 --> 16:13.840
ADULT ADAM: If I knew anything
about sports movies,

16:13.906 --> 16:16.909
this was the moment our hero
got an inspiring pep talk

16:16.976 --> 16:18.445
from the least likely
of places.

16:18.511 --> 16:19.946
On this day, it was me.

16:20.013 --> 16:23.050
Well, if there's one thing
I know, it's that
you can't just quit.

16:23.116 --> 16:24.951
Dude, enough with
your dumb sports movies.

16:25.018 --> 16:27.120
This isn't from a movie,
it's what I learned.

16:27.187 --> 16:31.724
Even if I don't ever
get a chance to play,
I can still help my team.

16:31.791 --> 16:33.960
Like how you filmed
the baseball games
like a weird creep.

16:34.027 --> 16:35.762
It's game film.
It helps them improve.

16:35.828 --> 16:37.764
Or like when the basketball
rolls under the bleachers

16:37.830 --> 16:38.865
and you climb under to get it.

16:38.931 --> 16:40.567
I fit in small spaces.

16:40.633 --> 16:43.970
So, even though
you're an unbearable loser
with no athletic ability

16:44.037 --> 16:46.539
and everyone talks about you
behind your back,

16:46.606 --> 16:48.308
you still find a way
to make a difference?

16:48.375 --> 16:50.243
And you can, too.

16:50.310 --> 16:51.344
Also, what?

16:51.411 --> 16:53.746
Thanks for
inspiring me, loser.

16:53.813 --> 16:55.715
Football team,
here I come.

16:57.184 --> 16:59.786
Thirty-one to nothing
in the first half.
What a disgrace!

16:59.852 --> 17:01.254
Coach, we're doing our best.

17:01.321 --> 17:03.890
Save the excuses
for Ruben Amaro Sr.,
Ruben Amaro Jr.

17:03.956 --> 17:07.960
